What is the projected market size & growth rate of the On-Board Charger Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global On-Board Charger Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the on-board charger market would exhibit a CAGR of 17.20% for the forecast period. Growing manufacturing rate of passenger vehicles around the globe on daily basis, increased demand of energy efficient transportation systems, growth and expansion of automotive industry especially in the developing economies and growing concerns regarding environmental pollution coupled with the global aim to reduce the carbon emissions are the major factors attributable to the growth of on-board charger market. Therefore, the market value would rocket up to USD 16.36 billion by 2029.

From the name itself, it is clear that the on-board chargers are used to convert the alternate current (AC) power to direct current (DC) voltage. On-board chargers are used to charge the battery packs in a vehicle which in turn transfers high kilowatts of power to the engine. In other words, on-board chargers are manufactured to charge and power the batteries of a vehicle. On-board chargers are generally designed for lower kilowatts of power transfer from the alternate current (AC) grid while the vehicle is parking.

Growth in the level of investments for research and development activities and rising number of electric stations especially in the developing economies will foster in growth in the on-board charger market value. Rising initiatives by the government to promote the manufacturing of electric vehicles coupled with rising modernization in the production techniques will also create lucrative growth opportunities for the on-board charger market. Growth in the technological advancements and growth in the demand from the emerging economies will also foster the on-board charger market growth. Growing expenditure by the government to strengthen the semiconductors industry will further carve the way for the growth of the on-board charger market.

However, lack of technological expertise in the developing and underdeveloped economies will pose a major challenge to the on-board charger market growth rate. High costs involved with technological innovations and rise in the cost of research and development activities will hamper the on-board charger market growth rate. Lack of standardization pertaining to electric vehicle charging will also restrict the scope of growth for the on-board charger market.

